WEBVTT

00:01.435 --> 00:03.668
♪ Da, da, da-ba-da, da, da,
ba-da-ba-da-ba ♪

00:03.703 --> 00:05.170
♪ Da, da, da-ba-da, da, da ♪
Let's go!

00:05.205 --> 00:06.872
♪ We'll be there ♪

00:06.907 --> 00:09.541
♪ A wink and a smile
and a great old time ♪

00:09.576 --> 00:11.743
♪ Yeah, we'll be there ♪

00:11.778 --> 00:13.845
♪ Wherever we are,
there's some fun to be found ♪

00:13.880 --> 00:16.181
♪ We'll be there
when you turn that corner ♪

00:16.216 --> 00:17.516
♪ We'll jump out the bush ♪

00:17.551 --> 00:19.217
♪ With a big bear hug
and a smile ♪

00:19.252 --> 00:20.686
♪ We'll be there ♪

00:26.760 --> 00:29.895
[ Machine beeping ]

00:29.930 --> 00:32.597
Hey, Grizz, let's get out of
here, man. I'm getting hungry.

00:32.632 --> 00:34.399
Ice Bear wants
to start cooking A.S.A.P.

00:34.434 --> 00:36.935
Hold on, guys,
- still looking for a movie.

00:36.970 --> 00:38.236
No.

00:38.271 --> 00:40.539
No. Oh, look! Ha.
They have "Justice Cop."

00:40.574 --> 00:42.441
-It's a pretty good collection.
-I don't know, man.

00:42.476 --> 00:44.176
These are all
pretty cheesy movies.

00:44.211 --> 00:45.577
Yeah, that's why
it's so good.

00:45.612 --> 00:48.080
"Drop your weapon
and surrender to justice!

00:48.115 --> 00:49.414
-Hmph!"
-[ Laughs ]

00:49.449 --> 00:51.883
That was pretty good.
Do another one.

00:51.918 --> 00:54.586
Director: Wait, what? W-What
do you mean, we have no bear?

00:54.621 --> 00:57.622
You know production starts
today. We need a bear!

00:57.657 --> 01:01.193
How do -- How do we make a movie
named "Grizzly" without a bear?

01:01.228 --> 01:03.895
-This is --
-[ Hooting ]

01:03.930 --> 01:05.797
Hmm. Let me call you back.

01:05.832 --> 01:07.632
[ Hooting ]

01:07.667 --> 01:08.900
[ Screeching ]

01:08.935 --> 01:10.268
-Beautiful!
-Huh?

01:10.303 --> 01:12.137
Just beautiful! Love it!

01:12.172 --> 01:14.372
Ah, bravo, bravo.

01:14.407 --> 01:16.274
Uh, is she clapping at us?

01:16.309 --> 01:18.443
Yeah, I'm clapping at you,
Grizzly Bear.

01:18.478 --> 01:20.278
Really dug
your performance there.

01:20.313 --> 01:22.747
-Do you like movies?
-Uh, yeah, sure.

01:22.782 --> 01:24.950
Well, guess what?
I'm a movie director.

01:24.985 --> 01:28.153
How would you like to be
in a movie about a grizzly bear?

01:28.188 --> 01:29.554
What? Really?

01:29.589 --> 01:31.123
Ice Bear would like to be
in cooking show.

01:31.158 --> 01:33.158
Dude, I've heard
of these scams before.

01:33.193 --> 01:34.893
They dazzle you
with all the sweet talk,

01:34.928 --> 01:37.129
and then they sell
your personal info!

01:37.164 --> 01:38.630
[ Scoffs ]
- What are you talking about?

01:38.665 --> 01:40.632
Here, take a look
at this script.

01:40.667 --> 01:42.234
Oh, huh.

01:42.269 --> 01:44.436
"Grizzly The Movie"?

01:44.471 --> 01:46.438
Holy moly!
They're finally making a movie

01:46.473 --> 01:48.140
about how awesome
grizzlies are!

01:48.175 --> 01:49.641
And I get to be the star?

01:49.676 --> 01:51.610
Uh, let me think about it.
I'm in!

01:51.645 --> 01:53.445
Cool. All right, then.

01:53.480 --> 01:54.913
This is gonna be
your first step

01:54.948 --> 01:57.849
to becoming
a worldwide superstar.

01:57.884 --> 01:59.484
Yeah!
[ Grunts ]

01:59.519 --> 02:01.987
-Ready to roll?
-Wait, can my brothers come?

02:02.022 --> 02:03.455
Hi. Heh.

02:03.490 --> 02:06.124
Mm, sure, as long
- as they don't get in the way.

02:06.159 --> 02:08.860
Yeah!
[ Laughs ]

02:08.895 --> 02:10.295
Ugh. Whew.

02:10.330 --> 02:13.031
-Okay. Let's go.
-Ice Bear is ready to roll.

02:13.066 --> 02:14.466
-Action.
-All right.

02:14.501 --> 02:15.901
[ Car door shuts ]

02:20.373 --> 02:22.474
Whoa.
This is amazing, Grizz.

02:22.509 --> 02:24.342
Ice Bear is happy
- to see his brother blow up.

02:24.377 --> 02:25.610
[ Laughs ]

02:25.645 --> 02:27.212
Ah, you haven't
seen anything yet.

02:27.247 --> 02:28.513
-Uh, sir?
-Huh?

02:28.548 --> 02:30.482
-Read this and sign, please.
-Oh, okay.

02:30.517 --> 02:32.484
Wait, Grizz, you should
really read through it.

02:32.519 --> 02:34.386
Hey, guys,
- check out our food table.

02:34.421 --> 02:35.854
-Did you guys eat yet?
-[ Gasps ]

02:35.889 --> 02:38.690
No, we haven't!
Oh, I was starving!

02:38.725 --> 02:40.358
[ Chuckles ]
- Have as much as you want.

02:40.393 --> 02:43.161
It's all yours.

02:43.196 --> 02:44.696
What's going on, Grizz?
You ready?

02:44.731 --> 02:46.998
Uh, yeah, I'm just trying
to understand what this is.

02:47.033 --> 02:48.867
You know, we're losing
a lot of time here.

02:48.902 --> 02:50.368
Remember,
the earlier you sign,

02:50.403 --> 02:53.371
the quicker you become
a worldwide superstar.

02:53.406 --> 02:54.673
-Up to you.
-Hey-hey!

02:54.708 --> 02:57.375
Then I'll sign it
right now, yo!

02:57.410 --> 03:00.679
Awesome.
- All right, everyone! Let's roll!

03:00.714 --> 03:02.747
Okay, this is
where you're gonna be.

03:02.782 --> 03:05.083
Cool. Cool.
Uh, hey, what's up, guys?

03:05.118 --> 03:07.385
I'm Grizz, you know,
main character of the movie.

03:07.420 --> 03:08.887
Oh, shoot,
I forgot my script.

03:08.922 --> 03:10.522
Oh, no need
to worry about that.

03:10.557 --> 03:12.424
You just need
to hide behind this bush

03:12.459 --> 03:14.426
and scare these guys here.

03:14.461 --> 03:16.394
-Pretty easy, huh?
-Psh, totally.

03:16.429 --> 03:19.064
-Okay, let's do this, then.
-Whoo!

03:19.099 --> 03:21.233
Ooh, hoo, hoo, hoo.

03:21.268 --> 03:23.235
Scene number 17, Shot 1.

03:23.270 --> 03:24.703
<i>Ready? Action!</i>

03:24.738 --> 03:27.572
[ Insects chirping, wolf howls ]

03:27.607 --> 03:29.574
[ Owl hooting ]

03:29.609 --> 03:31.610
Mm, well,
what do you think?

03:31.645 --> 03:33.411
I think it looks good.
Let's set camp.

03:33.446 --> 03:35.180
[ Whispering ]
All right, cue the bear.

03:35.215 --> 03:37.082
[ Rustling ]

03:37.117 --> 03:38.917
Boo! Ooh. Aah.

03:38.952 --> 03:40.952
I'm scary!

03:40.987 --> 03:42.254
Whoo-oo-ooh!

03:42.289 --> 03:44.923
Cut! Okay, okay,
that was great, Grizz,

03:44.958 --> 03:47.926
but I'm just curious
why you yelled "boo" there.

03:47.961 --> 03:50.095
I was trying to act like a
ghost, 'cause ghosts are scary.

03:50.130 --> 03:52.530
Was it too scary? Should I --
Should I try to pull it back?

03:52.565 --> 03:54.766
Yeah, but you don't need
to act like a ghost.

03:54.801 --> 03:57.135
I want to see
how<i> you</i> would scare them.

03:57.170 --> 03:58.937
Ah, gotcha. Mm, mm.

03:58.972 --> 04:01.706
Okay, more like me.
Got it.

04:01.741 --> 04:03.775
Yeah, this place looks good
to set camp.

04:03.810 --> 04:05.877
Hey! Hey, you,
get off my lawn!

04:05.912 --> 04:08.380
I'm an intimidating guy!
I'm in a gang,

04:08.415 --> 04:11.449
and I'm sick of you Millennials
trespassing on my property!

04:11.484 --> 04:13.251
-Cut!
-Cool. Is that a wrap?

04:13.286 --> 04:14.753
No, not quite there yet.

04:14.788 --> 04:17.055
Uh, why don't we try
something different, huh?

04:17.090 --> 04:20.225
[ Eating noisily ]

04:20.260 --> 04:22.727
Hey, let's go
sit over there.

04:22.762 --> 04:25.730
Hey, excuse me,
out of the way, please.

04:25.765 --> 04:27.232
Hey, here are some boxes.

04:27.267 --> 04:29.234
Hey, out of the way!

04:29.269 --> 04:31.069
Ready? Action!
[ Beep ]

04:31.104 --> 04:32.604
[ Laughs evilly ]

04:32.639 --> 04:35.140
Welcome to your doom!

04:35.175 --> 04:36.608
[ Beep ]
Nyah, nyah, nyah!

04:36.643 --> 04:37.809
[ Beep ]
Aah!

04:37.844 --> 04:40.078
Aah!

04:40.113 --> 04:41.279
Aah!

04:41.314 --> 04:42.647
You talkin' to me?

04:42.682 --> 04:44.316
Are you talking to me?!

04:44.351 --> 04:46.084
-One scary boss I am!
-Ugh. Cut!

04:46.119 --> 04:47.986
Huh? Did I get it?
- 'Cause -- 'Cause I-I can totally

04:48.021 --> 04:49.521
do another version
if you need one.

04:49.556 --> 04:50.989
I mean, if you think
that was perfect --

04:51.024 --> 04:52.857
Yeah, I think we can
fix this in post.

04:52.892 --> 04:56.194
Okay, cool, let's just try and
focus on the next scene, yeah?

04:56.229 --> 04:57.529
That was awesome, Grizz.

04:57.564 --> 05:00.498
-Whoo!
-Out of the way!

05:00.533 --> 05:01.966
Okay, come on in.
Don't be shy.

05:02.001 --> 05:04.002
Now, this next scene
is pretty straightforward.

05:04.037 --> 05:06.771
You are going to enter the
cabin, approach Mr. Ranger here,

05:06.806 --> 05:10.342
and then I need you to --
Hmm, how do I put it?

05:10.377 --> 05:12.844
Attack him! Really give him
the bear treatment.

05:12.879 --> 05:14.713
-You know what I mean?
-[ Laughing ] Oh.

05:14.748 --> 05:16.848
Oh, yeah. I think
I know what you mean.

05:16.883 --> 05:18.216
Excellent.
Let's get started.

05:18.251 --> 05:20.819
Ready on set! Prep the lights.
Sound's feeding?

05:20.854 --> 05:23.054
All right, Grizz
You got this.

05:23.089 --> 05:25.023
<i>And action!</i>

05:25.058 --> 05:28.193
[ Knock on door ]

05:28.228 --> 05:30.829
[ Gasps ]

05:30.864 --> 05:33.131
[ Growling ]

05:33.166 --> 05:34.866
Yah! Hah! Hyah!

05:34.901 --> 05:37.035
Cut!
Cut, cut, cut, cut!

05:37.070 --> 05:38.503
What's happening?
What is this?

05:38.538 --> 05:40.071
Was I kicking too much?
Okay, I'm sorry.

05:40.106 --> 05:41.873
I didn't know what kind
of karate you were looking for,

05:41.908 --> 05:43.241
and also, I wasn't sure
what belt level that guy was,

05:43.276 --> 05:44.642
-and I didn't want to overstep.
-No, no, no, no.

05:44.677 --> 05:46.044
Why would I want you
to do karate?

05:46.079 --> 05:49.414
I want you to maim him,
maul him like a bear would.

05:49.449 --> 05:51.082
Maul?
But I don't do that stuff.

05:51.117 --> 05:53.051
I mean like how
a more typical bear would.

05:53.086 --> 05:54.519
But my brothers
are bears, too,

05:54.554 --> 05:55.653
and they aren't
like that, either.

05:55.688 --> 05:56.921
-Out of the way!
-Sorry!

05:56.956 --> 05:58.923
-Make way.
-O-Okay. Where should we go?

05:58.958 --> 06:01.226
-Move it!
-Oh, for crying out loud.

06:01.261 --> 06:02.494
Hmm.

06:02.529 --> 06:04.028
Ma'am, there's always
the other option.

06:04.063 --> 06:06.698
-Andy's ready to go.
-That's it. Make it happen.

06:06.733 --> 06:08.233
Reset lighting!
Prep for take two!

06:08.268 --> 06:10.368
Now, don't worry.
- You just keep doing your thing.

06:10.403 --> 06:12.404
This is all gonna work out.

06:12.439 --> 06:14.205
Uh, okay.

06:14.240 --> 06:16.074
<i>Action!</i>

06:16.109 --> 06:17.675
[ Knock on door ]

06:17.710 --> 06:20.178
And freeze!
Bring in Andy!

06:20.213 --> 06:21.880
Andy? Whoa!

06:25.251 --> 06:26.384
Hey, i-is everything okay?

06:26.419 --> 06:27.719
I didn't get to try
my Jiu Jitsu.

06:27.754 --> 06:31.423
Don't worry.
It's all taken care of.

06:31.458 --> 06:33.224
[ Computer beeps ]

06:33.259 --> 06:34.592
<i>And action!</i>

06:34.627 --> 06:36.728
[ Bear roaring ]

06:39.299 --> 06:41.633
[ Ranger screaming,
cloth tearing ]

06:41.668 --> 06:43.368
[ Bear continues roaring ]

06:43.403 --> 06:45.703
No, please, not my leg!

06:45.738 --> 06:47.472
Oh, dear!

06:47.507 --> 06:49.374
No. Aah.

06:49.409 --> 06:52.043
No, no, no!

06:52.078 --> 06:54.779
[ Screams ]

06:54.814 --> 06:56.915
-Whoa, is that you?
-Cut!

06:56.950 --> 06:59.217
Cut!
That was perfect!

06:59.252 --> 07:01.152
Just the level of scary
we're going for.

07:01.187 --> 07:02.887
You know what?
Let's keep this energy going

07:02.922 --> 07:04.989
and jump straight ahead
to the big finale.

07:05.024 --> 07:06.791
Uh, excuse me,
Miss Director, ma'am?

07:06.826 --> 07:08.159
This just doesn't
feel right.

07:08.194 --> 07:10.762
Portraying grizzlies
like this is wrong.

07:10.797 --> 07:12.764
Most grizzlies
are really chill.

07:12.799 --> 07:14.799
That may be,
- but this isn't a chill movie.

07:14.834 --> 07:16.501
This is a scary movie.

07:16.536 --> 07:20.004
Grizzlies are gonna be the next
big thing everyone's afraid of.

07:20.039 --> 07:23.308
Well, I won't stand for that.
I refuse to be a part of this.

07:23.343 --> 07:25.643
Hmm. Okay, you're fired.

07:25.678 --> 07:28.146
Fired?
Well, if I'm fired,

07:28.181 --> 07:30.915
I won't let you use my face
for your movie, then. Hmph.

07:30.950 --> 07:32.817
Actually, you signed away
your face rights

07:32.852 --> 07:34.986
here in your contract,
so we can do whatever we want.

07:35.021 --> 07:36.821
Now, if you don't mind,
we have a film to make.

07:36.856 --> 07:38.690
-Security will escort you out.
-Wha-- Hey!

07:38.725 --> 07:40.091
Okay, this is wrong,
and you know it.

07:40.126 --> 07:42.193
<i>All right,</i>
- <i>we've got a finale to film!</i>

07:42.228 --> 07:44.329
<i>Bring out the final set piece!</i>
Don't do this! Grizzlies are nice.

07:44.364 --> 07:46.764
This is a poor representation
of my species.

07:46.799 --> 07:49.133
[ Grunting ]
All right, I'm going!

07:49.168 --> 07:50.768
<i>We need to move quick.</i>
<i>I don't care</i>

07:50.803 --> 07:52.604
<i>if it's up to code.</i>
<i>Get this --</i>

07:52.639 --> 07:54.339
[ Door slams ]

07:54.374 --> 07:57.042
[ Grumbling indistinctly ]
Stereotype.

07:58.912 --> 08:00.111
Don't let it
get to you, man.

08:00.146 --> 08:01.880
I mean, it's just
a movie, you know?

08:01.915 --> 08:04.282
Oh, sure. I mean,
- it starts as just a movie,

08:04.317 --> 08:06.451
but then people get sucked
into that narrow point of view,

08:06.486 --> 08:08.353
and next thing you know,
everyone's afraid of --

08:08.388 --> 08:11.189
-Check it out.
-Whoa, that's gnarly.

08:11.224 --> 08:14.492
Bears really are
- the scariest animal ever.

08:14.527 --> 08:16.394
-Oh! Aah!
-Aah! Aah!

08:16.429 --> 08:17.795
Um, what's their problem?

08:17.830 --> 08:20.031
See? It's not just
affecting us, man.

08:20.066 --> 08:23.301
This portrayal is affecting
all bears, including you guys.

08:23.336 --> 08:25.169
People are gonna watch this
on their movie nights

08:25.204 --> 08:27.005
and think all bears
are actually like this.

08:27.040 --> 08:28.573
-It's coming down!
-Whoa! Look out!

08:28.608 --> 08:29.874
What's that sound?

08:29.909 --> 08:31.309
Is that coming
from the "Grizzly" set?

08:31.344 --> 08:33.545
Ice Bear senses
impending code violations.

08:33.580 --> 08:35.380
[ Rumbling ]

08:35.415 --> 08:36.714
Man:
Oh, no. Oh, no.

08:36.749 --> 08:38.149
-[ Screaming ]
-Oh, my gosh! What do we do?

08:38.184 --> 08:40.485
-What do we do? What do we do?
-Whoa. Oh, no!

08:40.520 --> 08:43.555
[ Rumbling continues ]

08:43.590 --> 08:44.722
-Aah!
-Look out!

08:44.757 --> 08:46.891
[ Thud ]
Andy!

08:46.926 --> 08:48.693
Aah! Help. I'm stuck.

08:48.728 --> 08:50.028
-Aah!
-Oh, my gosh! What do we do?

08:50.063 --> 08:51.563
What do we do?
What do we do?

08:51.598 --> 08:53.998
This place is falling apart.
We should do something.

08:54.033 --> 08:56.568
Okay, I'm gonna get Andy.
You guys move everyone outside.

08:56.603 --> 08:58.203
Ice Bear got this.

08:59.706 --> 09:00.838
Whoa! Aah!

09:00.873 --> 09:03.041
[ Grunting ]

09:06.613 --> 09:07.879
Look out below!

09:07.914 --> 09:10.081
Out of the way!

09:10.116 --> 09:11.015
Move.

09:11.050 --> 09:15.920
Move, move,
move, move, move it!

09:15.955 --> 09:17.855
[ Crying ]
Help me.

09:17.890 --> 09:21.225
Don't worry, Andy.
I'm gonna get you down.

09:21.260 --> 09:23.128
[ Grunting ]

09:27.634 --> 09:29.400
Hurry!

09:29.435 --> 09:31.603
-Ice Bear moved everyone.
-What about Grizz?

09:31.638 --> 09:34.072
Aah!
[ Crashing ]

09:36.309 --> 09:38.776
Grizz!

09:38.811 --> 09:40.845
[ Gasps ]

09:42.315 --> 09:45.317
♪♪

09:50.156 --> 09:52.223
-Thank you for saving me.
-Don't mention it.

09:52.258 --> 09:55.393
-Grizz, you're all right.
-Eh, nothing I couldn't handle.

09:55.428 --> 09:57.762
[ Cheers and applause ]

09:59.632 --> 10:01.966
Yes!
That was amazing!

10:02.001 --> 10:05.837
That's what audiences want --
action, heroism, bravery.

10:05.872 --> 10:07.305
Look, I know we had
our differences,

10:07.340 --> 10:09.307
what with the whole
firing thing,

10:09.342 --> 10:11.643
but how would you like
to make this film right?

10:11.678 --> 10:14.812
No more CGI,
just Grizz the hero.

10:14.847 --> 10:16.481
What do you say?

10:16.516 --> 10:17.815
Hmm.

10:17.850 --> 10:20.118
-All right, I'll do it.
-All right.

10:20.153 --> 10:21.653
♪♪

10:21.688 --> 10:23.221
[ Gasps ]

10:25.358 --> 10:26.824
Ranger to dispatch.

10:26.859 --> 10:29.193
It's not a monster.

10:29.228 --> 10:31.329
It's a friend.

10:31.364 --> 10:32.697
[ Tink! ]

10:32.732 --> 10:36.034
♪♪

10:36.069 --> 10:38.436
Whoo-hoo-hoo! Yeah!
[ Laughs ]

10:38.471 --> 10:40.038
That was amazing.
What'd you guys think?

10:40.073 --> 10:41.606
That was so much fun!

10:41.641 --> 10:43.975
Ice Bear appreciates they didn't
force romantic subplot.

10:44.010 --> 10:45.343
Thanks, you guys. Oh.

10:45.378 --> 10:48.813
Well, I wonder
how everyone else liked it.

10:48.848 --> 10:49.947
Oh, no.

10:49.982 --> 10:51.883
[ Sighs ]
I guess it was a flop?

10:51.918 --> 10:53.818
Kid:
Whoo-hoo! I loved it!

10:53.853 --> 10:55.720
Yeah, bears are awesome!

10:55.755 --> 10:58.390
Hey, this movie's PG-13.
Get out of here!

11:01.160 --> 11:02.360
Progress!

11:04.230 --> 11:07.232
♪♪
